The Opportunity

We are seeking a talented and passionate Data Scientist to join our growing team. In this role, you will play a key part in extracting valuable insights from our data to drive informed decision-making across the organization. You will work closely with various teams, including engineering, product, and marketing, to develop and implement data-driven solutions that address critical business challenges.

Minimum Qualifications

Master's degree in Statistics, Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related field (or Bachelor's degree with relevant experience)
2+ years of experience in a data science or related role (minimum; adjust based on your needs)
Strong proficiency in programming languages like Python (including libraries like NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn) and SQL
Essential Skills

Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
Ability to design, develop, and implement machine learning models
Experience with data wrangling, cleaning, and transformation
Strong statistical and mathematical background
Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, to effectively present insights to technical and non-technical audiences
Ability to work independently as well as collaboratively in a team environment
Desired Skills

Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP)
Experience with big data technologies (e.g., Spark)
Experience with deep learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch)
Experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI)
Benefits

Competitive salary and benefits package
Opportunity to work on challenging and impactful projects
Collaborative and supportive work environment
Continuous learning and development opportunities